definition: abbr. for 克羅地亞|克罗地亚[Ke4 luo2 di4 ya4], Croatia/(Tw) abbr. for 克羅埃西亞|克罗埃西亚[Ke4 luo2 ai1 xi1 ya4], Croatia

pinyin: Ang4 ge2 lu3 Sa4 ke4 xun4

sentences.english: He rep laced the weak Saxon rule with a strong Norman government.
sentences.chinese: 他用強有力的諾曼政府代替了軟弱的薩克遜政府。

sentences.english: He replaced the weak Saxon rule with a strong Norman government. He replaced the weak Saxon rule with a strong Norman government.
sentences.chinese: 他用強有力的諾曼政府代替了軟弱的薩克遜政府。

sentences.english: Even perfidious Anglo - Saxons agree on the need for change.
sentences.chinese: 即使是無信的安格魯薩克遜人也同意這種改革。

sentences.english: While Anglo-Saxons were throwing money around, Germans kept saving.
sentences.chinese: 當盎格魯薩克遜人到處花錢之時，德國人保持儲蓄。
